direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods generate ID numbers but with different validity outcomes (valid vs. invalid).
The generateValid method relies on the isValidSwedishSsn method to ensure the generated ID number is valid.
Both methods involve calculations on strings to produce a result, with similar control flows and exception handling.
Both methods handle date parsing and potential exceptions in a similar manner.
Both methods access and manipulate patterns for generating ID numbers.
The default implementation of generateValid in the IdNumberGenerator interface can be substituted with the implementation in SwedenIdNumber.
